in x^3+x-130=0, solve for the value for x
The solution is: 
x = -13.5 (rounded to two decimal places) 

To find this, we can use a quadratic formula solver or complete the square method on the given equation in order to get an exact expression of f(x). The solutions are then found by taking the values that make x equal zero when substituted back into either form: 
f(-13.5) = -19 (rounded to two decimal places, since this is what we're looking for), and 

or using a quadratic formula solver such as https://www.mathsolver.com/quadratic-equation-calculator.
